.TH "mpol_to_str" 9 "mpol_to_str" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mpol_to_str \- format a mempolicy structure for printing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" mpol_to_str
.BI "(char *buffer "  ","
.BI "int maxlen "  ","
.BI "struct mempolicy *pol "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buffer" 12
to contain formatted mempolicy string
.IP "maxlen" 12
length of \fIbuffer\fP
.IP "pol" 12
pointer to mempolicy to be formatted
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Convert \fIpol\fP into a string.  If \fIbuffer\fP is too short, truncate the string.
Recommend a \fImaxlen\fP of at least 32 for the longest mode, "interleave", the
longest flag, "relative", and to display at least a few node ids.
